  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Pet Groomer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>PAWSITIVE IMAGE LLP, a new grooming destination to pamper your pets. We believe in creating a positive image for lovable pals. Pet grooming with love, one dog at a time.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will deliver professional grooming services for dogs and cats, ensuring their health and comfort while maintaining a clean and safe environment. You will engage with clients to address their pets’ needs and contribute to their overall well-being.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform comprehensive grooming services for dogs and cats, including bathing, drying, brushing, trimming, and clipping fur to meet breed-specific standards</li><li>Inspect pets for skin or coat conditions and promptly communicate any concerns to owners or veterinarians to ensure timely care</li><li>Maintain cleanliness and safety of the grooming workspace and equipment to uphold hygiene standards</li><li>Address client concerns and requests effectively to provide a positive customer experience and build trust</li><li>Apply diverse grooming techniques tailored to different breeds to achieve high-quality grooming outcomes</li><li>Monitor pet behavior and health indicators during grooming sessions to identify signs of distress or illness and respond appropriately</li><li>Collaborate with team members and work independently to manage grooming schedules and deliver consistent service quality</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Certification from a recognized grooming program</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>At least 2 years of experience in grooming dogs and cats</li><li>Knowledge of pet health and behavior, particularly signs of distress or illness</li><li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills to engage with clients and team members</li><li>Demonstrated passion for animals and commitment to their well-being</li></ul>",
